CSRF => CROSS SITE REQUEST FORGERY

- Hacker tricks users into making request to THRID PARTY/HACKER'S SERVER on behalf of User.

- They can be used for fraudulent request on your website from USER through HACKER.

- Most harmful is: Hacker can access logged in state of USER and starts requesting to your page on behalf of USER.


HOW TO SOLVE?

- GET request should be make any changes like Password, Bank acc. no., address, etc.
- Use POST request for making any changes
- Store form TOKEN in user's session | also store TOKEN generation time to see it is NEW/RECENT or NOT
- Add hidden field in form with form token as value